      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): bound JSON/text response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross OpenAI realtime/oauth/image-generation/embedding-batch providers\n(6 call sites in 4 files).\n\n## Changes\n\nEach site uses a file-local constant and a descriptive overflow error message.\nNo new abstraction — reuses the shared `media-core` bounded reader.\n\n| File | Sites |\n|------|------:|\n| `extensions/openai/embedding-batch.ts` | 2 |\n| `extensions/openai/image-generation-provider.ts` | 1 |\n| `extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.ts` | 1 |\n| `extensions/openai/realtime-provider-shared.ts` | 1 |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Untrusted OpenAI API responses must not be buffered\n  whole; the read must stop at the 1 MiB cap, cancel the stream, and throw a\n  bounded error — while valid small responses still parse unchanged.\n- **Real environment tested**: A real `node:http` server streaming\n  Content-Length-less JSON bodies (advertised ~64 MiB, well above the 1 MiB cap).\n  The real `readResponseWithLimit` from the production `media-core` package was\n  driven against it — real `fetch()`, real TCP socket, real bounded reader.\n  Node v22.12.0.\n- **What was not tested**: Did not hit the live `api.openai.com` endpoint.\n\n## Evidence\n### Real HTTP proof (against live server)\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\n[proof] real server, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error :: msg=\"Error: JSON response exceeds 1048576 bytes\"\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\nThe proof harness starts a real `node:http` server with no Content-Length,\nstreams ~64 MiB of JSON, and verifies `readResponseWithLimit` cancels the\nstream at the 1 MiB cap. The negative control proves the cap is load-bearing.\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/openai/\n  Test Files  27 passed (27)\n       Tests  331 passed (331)\n```\n\n**Label**: security\n\n_AI-assisted._\n",
